e planets: in disks with $\\beta \\approx 0.1$ -- $1$, a\nnear-thermal mass planet opens only a single wide gap around its orbit, in\ncontrast to the several narrow gaps produced when cooling is either faster or\nslower.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 4 Nov 2019 19:00:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 24 Feb 2020 20:30:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-04-08"}
